<TITLE> Emily rested for a week </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 30 (bdnews24.com)  National striker Jahid Hasan Emily has been advised to take week's rest following his hamstring injury sustained in the Super Cup final between Mohammedan Sporting Club and Dhaka Abahani. "Emily has been rested for a week and we will see how he improves later," said national football team manager Imtiaz Sultan Johnny on Monday during the team's practice at the Bangabandhu National Stadium. Striker Hedayetul Robin also skipped the second day of training though he was present and he was only confined to running following his knee injury. Except Emily and Robin, 23 national players split into different groups practised under the supervision of new Brazilian coach Edson Silva Dido, who was assisted by coach Shafiqul Islam Manik, Argentine trainer Ariel Colman and goalkeeping coach Ponir. The federation also temporarily appointed physio Daliur Rahman, who received training from Australia, for one moth ahead of the AFC Challenge Cup to be held in Bangladesh from April 26 to 30. Apart from the match fees, the players will also get Tk 10,000 each as working allowance and another Tk 15,000 to buy a pair of boots, said Badal Roy, national team management committee chairman and BFF vice-president. bd
